ich provides an HTTP API server for managing `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` custom resources in the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group.\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md:\n  Line 1: # Proposal: AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器\n  Line 5: Implement a Kubernetes Reconciler controller in `pkg/workloadmanager` to provide native, declarative lifecycle management for `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` custom resources. This transforms the current imperative HTTP API into a Kubernetes-native controller pattern that automatically reconciles desired state with actual cluster state.\n  Line 53: pkg/workloadmanager/\n  Line 106: | github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager | local | Existing WorkloadManager |\n  Line 193: **Approach**: Implement controller as a separate microservice not embedded in workloadmanager.\n  Line 201: - Duplicated code with existing workloadmanager\n  Line 203: **Decision**: Rejected — tightly coupling with workloadmanager provides better resource sharing and simpler deployment.\n  Line 259: - [ ] Controller integrates with existing workloadmanager deployment\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-007/delta-spec.md:\n  Line 1: # Delta Spec: AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器\n  Line 5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the Kubernetes Reconciler controller in `pkg/workloadmanager`. The Reconciler is responsible for watching and reconciling Sandbox custom resources with actual Kubernetes resources (Pods, Services, ConfigMaps), ensuring the desired state matches the actual cluster state.\n  Line 9: - **AR**: AR-007\n  Line 10: - **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n  Line 19: ### AR-007-001: Reconciler Startup\n  Line 21: - **GIVEN** the workloadmanager service starting\n  Line 28: ### AR-007-002: Reconcile Create Event\n  Line 40: ### AR-007-003: Reconcile